arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for a university course catalog. The project has already been scaffolded at:
`/tmp/sv-da6cad83ff264573b296c4f8b0786f42/UniversityCourseCatalog`

It was created with `dotnet new blazor -int None` (Static SSR, no interactive runtime).

## CRITICAL SSR RULES
- Do NOT use `@rendermode` anywhere
- Do NOT use `@onclick` or any event handlers — they require interactive mode
- Forms use standard HTML `<form method="get">` for search/filter or `<form method="post">` with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` and `<AntiforgeryToken />` for submissions
- Use `[SupplyParameterFromQuery]` for query string parameters (search, filter)
- Navigation is via `<a href="...">` links, not NavigationManager
- No `IJSRuntime`

## What to build

### 1. Data Model & Service
Create `Models/` and `Services/` folders in the project root.

**Models/Course.cs:**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Course
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string CourseCode { get; set; } = "";
    public string Title { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
